overview: The user initiated a request to evaluate an existing sleep
  questionnaire codebase against a provided Statement of Work. The primary goal
  was to plan the implementation of a database for storing questionnaire
  responses, a mechanism for CSV data export, and a simple admin dashboard for
  client access, including any required authentication middleware. After
  reviewing the codebase, it was determined that while the questionnaire flow
  and PDF generation were in place, database storage, data retrieval, and an
  admin dashboard were missing. Key decisions were made regarding authentication
  complexity, opting for a simple password-based system, and clarifying
  demographic data collection to combine SOW requirements with existing fields.
  The resulting plan details the necessary updates to the demographics section,
  the creation of a  model in Prisma, the development of
  API endpoints for saving and retrieving data, the implementation of a
  lightweight authentication system, and the construction of the admin
  dashboard. NeonDB (PostgreSQL) was confirmed as the chosen database solution,
  integrated via Prisma.
